meta {
  name: Edit eval tasks
  type: http
  seq: 10
}

patch {
  url: {{host}}/tracer/eval-task/update_eval_task/
  body: json
  auth: bearer
}

auth:bearer {
  token: {{access_token}}
}

body:json {
  {
      "name": "test2",
      "spansLimit": 7,
      "samplingRate": 50,
      "evals": [
          "0dfc07f8-40d3-4fbe-a915-90624fec09d6",
          "33af790e-d176-4876-b3bb-c088ef1819bf",
          "a6e0c8fe-4f40-4195-9000-1edd07632c62",
          "c2e03a62-0479-4ed3-8ac6-077177e47575",
          "251c72e9-1444-45d6-a461-6d3a432c333b"
      ],
      "runType": "historical",
      "filters": {
          "project_id": "41503414-f181-455f-90bc-e6cd5b89f50a",
          "observationType": [
              "agent"
          ],
          "dateRange": [
              "2024-11-08T10:04:37.000Z",
              "2025-05-08T18:29:59.000Z"
          ]
      },
      "eval_task_id": "75d45a37-35f5-4423-b687-a4fea9c00d95",
    "edit_type": "edit_rerun"
  }
}

docs {
  For deleting and starting fresh: use edit_type = "fresh_run" and for edit and rerun, use edit_type = "edit_rerun"
  Change spans_limit and sampling rate to check  following behaviour:
  1. When span limit and sampling rate is unchanged, eval is added, new eval runs on processed spans
  2. When span limit is increased, sampling rate is unchanged, eval is added, existing eval runs on new spans only(span limit - processed spans) while new eval runs on all
  3. When span limit is decreased, sampling rate is unchanged, eval is added, new evals runs on a sample of processed spans of sample size min(span limit, sampling rate)
  4. When span limit is unchanged, sampling rate is increased, eval is added, new evals runs on new spans if max spans > old SR and max spans <= SR
  5. When span limit is unchanged, sampling rate is decreased, eval is added, new evals runs on sample of processed spns = sample size
  6. When span limit is increased, sampling rate is decreased, eval is added, new evals runs only if old max spans < new sampling rate
  7. When span limit is increased, sampling rate is increased, eval is added, new evals runs on min(max spans, sampling rate)-processed_spans
  8. When span limit is decreased, sampling rate is increased, eval is added, new evals runs on sample of processed spans,sample size= span limit
  9. When span limit is decreased,sampling rate is decreased, eval is added, new evals runs on sample of processed spans, sample size = min(span limit, sapling rate)

  To check removal of evals from task and observe homepage, remove id of eval from payload and update task

  10. New continous task now runs only on spans added after task creation
  11. Continous task doesn’t update to pending for each cycle until repicked
  12. Pause and unpause apis are working
}
